1.name: Add Cookie
1.doc: <p>Adds a cookie to your current session. "name" and "value" are required, "path", "domain" and "secure" are optional</p>

2.name: Add Location Strategy

6.name: Checkbox Should Be Selected
6.doc:
<p>Verifies checkbox identified by <span class="name">locator</span> is selected/checked.</p>
<p>Key attributes for checkboxes are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

7.name: Checkbox Should Not Be Selected
7.doc:
<p>Verifies checkbox identified by <span class="name">locator</span> is not selected/checked.</p>
<p>Key attributes for checkboxes are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

8.name: Choose Cancel On Next Confirmation
8.doc: <p>Cancel will be selected the next time <a href="#Confirm%20Action" class="name">Confirm Action</a> is used.</p>

9.name: Choose File

10.name: Choose Ok On Next Confirmation
10.doc:
<p>Undo the effect of using keywords <a href="#Choose%20Cancel%20On%20Next%20Confirmation" class="name">Choose Cancel On Next Confirmation</a>. Note that Selenium's overridden window.confirm() function will normally automatically return true, as if the user had manually clicked OK, so you shouldn't need to use this command unless for some reason you need to change your mind prior to the next confirmation. After any confirmation, Selenium will resume using the default behavior for future confirmations, automatically returning true (OK) unless/until you explicitly use <a href="#Choose%20Cancel%20On%20Next%20Confirmation" class="name">Choose Cancel On Next Confirmation</a> for each confirmation.</p>
<p>Note that every time a confirmation comes up, you must consume it by using a keywords such as <a href="#Get%20Alert%20Message" class="name">Get Alert Message</a>, or else the following selenium operations will fail.</p>

11.name: Clear Element Text
11.doc:
<p>Clears the text value of text entry element identified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

12.name: Click Button
12.doc:
<p>Clicks a button identified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>Key attributes for buttons are <span class="name">id</span>, <span class="name">name</span> and <span class="name">value</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

13.name: Click Element
13.doc:
<p>Click element identified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>Key attributes for arbitrary elements are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

14.name: Click Element At Coordinates
14.doc:
<p>Click element identified by <span class="name">locator</span> at x/y coordinates of the element. Cursor is moved and the center of the element and x/y coordinates are calculted from that point.</p>
<p>Key attributes for arbitrary elements are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

15.name: Click Image
15.doc:
<p>Clicks an image found by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>Key attributes for images are <span class="name">id</span>, <span class="name">src</span> and <span class="name">alt</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

16.name: Click Link
16.doc:
<p>Clicks a link identified by locator.</p>
<p>Key attributes for links are <span class="name">id</span>, <span class="name">name</span>, <span class="name">href</span> and link text. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

17.name: Close All Browsers

20.name: Confirm Action

21.name: Create Webdriver

22.name: Current Frame Contains
22.doc:
<p>Verifies that current frame contains <span class="name">text</span>.</p>
<p>See <a href="#Page%20Should%20Contain" class="name">Page Should Contain </a> for explanation about <span class="name">loglevel</span> argument.</p>

23.name: Current Frame Should Not Contain
23.doc:
<p>Verifies that current frame contains <span class="name">text</span>.</p>
<p>See <a href="#Page%20Should%20Contain" class="name">Page Should Contain </a> for explanation about <span class="name">loglevel</span> argument.</p>

25.name: Delete Cookie
25.doc:
<p>Deletes cookie matching <span class="name">name</span>.</p>
<p>If the cookie is not found, nothing happens.</p>

26.name: Dismiss Alert
26.doc:
<p>Returns true if alert was confirmed, false if it was dismissed</p>
<p>This keyword will fail if no alert is present. Note that following keywords will fail unless the alert is dismissed by this keyword or another like <a href="#Get%20Alert%20Message" class="name">Get Alert Message</a>.</p>

27.name: Double Click Element
27.doc:
<p>Double click element identified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>Key attributes for arbitrary elements are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

28.name: Drag And Drop

29.name: Drag And Drop By Offset

30.name: Element Should Be Disabled
30.doc:
<p>Verifies that element identified with <span class="name">locator</span> is disabled.</p>
<p>Key attributes for arbitrary elements are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

31.name: Element Should Be Enabled
31.doc:
<p>Verifies that element identified with <span class="name">locator</span> is enabled.</p>
<p>Key attributes for arbitrary elements are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

41.name: Get Alert Message
41.doc:
<p>Returns the text of current JavaScript alert.</p>
<p>By default the current JavaScript alert will be dismissed. This keyword will fail if no alert is present. Note that following keywords will fail unless the alert is dismissed by this keyword or another like <a href="#Get%20Alert%20Message" class="name">Get Alert Message</a>.</p>

42.name: Get All Links
42.doc:
<p>Returns a list containing ids of all links found in current page.</p>
<p>If a link has no id, an empty string will be in the list instead.</p>

43.name: Get Cookie Value
43.doc:
<p>Returns value of cookie found with <span class="name">name</span>.</p>
<p>If no cookie is found with <span class="name">name</span>, this keyword fails.</p>

44.name: Get Cookies
44.doc: <p>Returns all cookies of the current page.</p>

45.name: Get Element Attribute
45.doc:
<p>Return value of element attribute.</p>
<p><span class="name">attribute_locator</span> consists of element locator followed by an @ sign and attribute name, for example "element_id@class".</p>

46.name: Get Element Size
46.doc:
<p>Returns width and height of element identified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>The element width and height is returned. Fails if a matching element is not found.</p>

47.name: Get Horizontal Position

48.name: Get List Items
48.doc:
<p>Returns the values in the select list identified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>Select list keywords work on both lists and combo boxes. Key attributes for select lists are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

50.name: Get Matching Xpath Count

51.name: Get Selected List Label
51.doc:
<p>Returns the visible label of the selected element from the select list identified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>Select list keywords work on both lists and combo boxes. Key attributes for select lists are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

52.name: Get Selected List Labels

53.name: Get Selected List Value

54.name: Get Selected List Values

55.name: Get Selenium Implicit Wait
55.doc:
<p>Gets the wait in seconds that is waited by Selenium.</p>
<p>See <a href="#Set%20Selenium%20Implicit%20Wait" class="name">Set Selenium Implicit Wait</a> for an explanation.</p>

56.name: Get Selenium Speed
56.doc:
<p>Gets the delay in seconds that is waited after each Selenium command.</p>
<p>See <a href="#Set%20Selenium%20Speed" class="name">Set Selenium Speed</a> for an explanation.</p>

57.name: Get Selenium Timeout
57.doc:
<p>Gets the timeout in seconds that is used by various keywords.</p>
<p>See <a href="#Set%20Selenium%20Timeout" class="name">Set Selenium Timeout</a> for an explanation.</p>

58.name: Get Source
58.doc: <p>Returns the entire html source of the current page or frame.</p>

59.name: Get Table Cell

60.name: Get Text
60.doc:
<p>Returns the text value of element identified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

62.name: Get Value
62.doc:
<p>Returns the value attribute of element identified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

63.name: Get Vertical Position

64.name: Get Webelement
64.doc:
<p>Returns the first WebElement matching the given locator.</p>
<p>See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

65.name: Get Webelements
65.doc:
<p>Returns list of WebElement objects matching locator.</p>
<p>See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

66.name: Get Window Identifiers
66.doc: <p>Returns and logs id attributes of all windows known to the browser.</p>

67.name: Get Window Names
67.doc: <p>Returns and logs names of all windows known to the browser.</p>

68.name: Get Window Position

69.name: Get Window Size

70.name: Get Window Titles
70.doc: <p>Returns and logs titles of all windows known to the browser.</p>

71.name: Go Back
71.doc: <p>Simulates the user clicking the "back" button on their browser.</p>

72.name: Go To
72.doc: <p>Navigates the active browser instance to the provided URL.</p>

73.name: Input Password
73.doc:
<p>Types the given password into text field identified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>Difference between this keyword and <a href="#Input%20Text" class="name">Input Text</a> is that this keyword does not log the given password. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

74.name: Input Text
74.doc:
<p>Types the given <span class="name">text</span> into text field identified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

76.name: List Selection Should Be

77.name: List Should Have No Selections
77.doc:
<p>Verifies select list identified by <span class="name">locator</span> has no selections.</p>
<p>Select list keywords work on both lists and combo boxes. Key attributes for select lists are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

78.name: List Windows
78.doc: <p>Return all current window handles as a list</p>

81.name: Locator Should Match X Times

83.name: Log Source
83.doc:
<p>Logs and returns the entire html source of the current page or frame.</p>
<p>The <span class="name">loglevel</span> argument defines the used log level. Valid log levels are WARN, INFO (default), DEBUG, and NONE (no logging).</p>

84.name: Log Title
84.doc: <p>Logs and returns the title of current page.</p>

86.name: Mouse Down

87.name: Mouse Down On Image
87.doc:
<p>Simulates a mouse down event on an image.</p>
<p>Key attributes for images are <span class="name">id</span>, <span class="name">src</span> and <span class="name">alt</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

88.name: Mouse Down On Link
88.doc:
<p>Simulates a mouse down event on a link.</p>
<p>Key attributes for links are <span class="name">id</span>, <span class="name">name</span>, <span class="name">href</span> and link text. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

89.name: Mouse Out
89.doc:
<p>Simulates moving mouse away from the element specified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>Key attributes for arbitrary elements are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

90.name: Mouse Over
90.doc:
<p>Simulates hovering mouse over the element specified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>Key attributes for arbitrary elements are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

91.name: Mouse Up
91.doc:
<p>Simulates releasing the left mouse button on the element specified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>Key attributes for arbitrary elements are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

92.name: Open Browser

93.name: Open Context Menu
93.doc: <p>Opens context menu on element identified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>

94.name: Page Should Contain
94.doc:
<p>Verifies that current page contains <span class="name">text</span>.</p>
<p>If this keyword fails, it automatically logs the page source using the log level specified with the optional <span class="name">loglevel</span> argument. Valid log levels are DEBUG, INFO (default), WARN, and NONE. If the log level is NONE or below the current active log level the source will not be logged.</p>

103.doc:
<p>Verifies the current page does not contain <span class="name">text</span>.</p>
<p>See <a href="#Page%20Should%20Contain" class="name">Page Should Contain </a> for explanation about <span class="name">loglevel</span> argument.</p>

113.name: Radio Button Should Be Set To
113.doc:
<p>Verifies radio button group identified by <span class="name">group_name</span> has its selection set to <span class="name">value</span>.</p>
<p>See <a href="#Select%20Radio%20Button" class="name">Select Radio Button</a> for information about how radio buttons are located.</p>

114.name: Radio Button Should Not Be Selected
114.doc:
<p>Verifies radio button group identified by <span class="name">group_name</span> has no selection.</p>
<p>See <a href="#Select%20Radio%20Button" class="name">Select Radio Button</a> for information about how radio buttons are located.</p>

115.name: Register Keyword To Run On Failure

117.name: Remove Location Strategy
117.doc:
<p>Removes a previously added custom location strategy. Will fail if a default strategy is specified.</p>
<p>See <a href="#Add%20Location%20Strategy" class="name">Add Location Strategy</a> for details about adding a custom location strategy.</p>

118.name: Select All From List
118.doc:
<p>Selects all values from multi-select list identified by <span class="name">id</span>.</p>
<p>Key attributes for lists are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

119.name: Select Checkbox
119.doc:
<p>Selects checkbox identified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>Does nothing if checkbox is already selected. Key attributes for checkboxes are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

120.name: Select Frame
120.doc:
<p>Sets frame identified by <span class="name">locator</span> as current frame.</p>
<p>Key attributes for frames are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name.</span> See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

121.name: Select From List

122.name: Select From List By Index
122.doc:
<p>Selects <span class="name">*indexes</span> from list identified by <span class="name">locator</span></p>
<p>Select list keywords work on both lists and combo boxes. Key attributes for select lists are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

123.name: Select From List By Label
123.doc:
<p>Selects <span class="name">*labels</span> from list identified by <span class="name">locator</span></p>
<p>Select list keywords work on both lists and combo boxes. Key attributes for select lists are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

124.name: Select From List By Value
124.doc:
<p>Selects <span class="name">*values</span> from list identified by <span class="name">locator</span></p>
<p>Select list keywords work on both lists and combo boxes. Key attributes for select lists are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

128.name: Set Screenshot Directory
128.doc:
<p>Sets the root output directory for captured screenshots.</p>
<p><code>path</code> argument specifies the absolute path where the screenshots should be written to. If the specified <code>path</code> does not exist, it will be created. Setting <code>persist</code> specifies that the given <code>path</code> should be used for the rest of the test execution, otherwise the path will be restored at the end of the currently executing scope.</p>

135.doc:
<p>Submits a form identified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>If <span class="name">locator</span> is empty, first form in the page will be submitted. Key attributes for forms are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

148.doc:
<p>Removes selection of checkbox identified by <span class="name">locator</span>.</p>
<p>Does nothing if the checkbox is not checked. Key attributes for checkboxes are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

149.name: Unselect Frame
149.doc: <p>Sets the top frame as the current frame.</p>

150.name: Unselect From List

151.name: Unselect From List By Index
151.doc:
<p>Unselects <span class="name">*indexes</span> from list identified by <span class="name">locator</span></p>
<p>Select list keywords work on both lists and combo boxes. Key attributes for select lists are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

152.name: Unselect From List By Label
152.doc:
<p>Unselects <span class="name">*labels</span> from list identified by <span class="name">locator</span></p>
<p>Select list keywords work on both lists and combo boxes. Key attributes for select lists are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>

153.name: Unselect From List By Value
153.doc:
<p>Unselects <span class="name">*values</span> from list identified by <span class="name">locator</span></p>
<p>Select list keywords work on both lists and combo boxes. Key attributes for select lists are <span class="name">id</span> and <span class="name">name</span>. See <a href="#Introduction" class="name">introduction</a> for details about locating elements.</p>
